headline.main: AMBULANCE DRIVERS DEPART FOR AFRICA; Seven Young Americans Fly to Miami on First Leg of Trip

lead_paragraph: Bound for Africa, where they will serve as ambulance drivers with the British Army, seven young Americans, all members of the American Field Service, left La Guardia Field yesterday aboard Miami-bound planes of the Eastern Air Lines. Six of the young men left together on a plane at 10:30 A.M., while the seventh, Oscar C. Sewall of Dublin, N.H., second in command, departed on an afternoon flight.
abstract: Aid to Brit: 7 Amer Field Service volunteers leave N Y C to serve as ambulance drivers with Brit Army in Africa
